---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import CTA from '../../components/CTA.astro';
import FAQ from '../../components/FAQ.astro';

const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'How far is Altered Air from Peoria?',
    a: 'About 35–40 minutes from our Buckeye shop, depending on where in Peoria. Peoria is a large city that stretches well north along the 101, and the northern communities (Vistancia, Lake Pleasant area) are a bit further than the southern ones (P83, Bell Road). We make the drive regularly and treat Peoria as a full service area. Call <a href="tel:+17605941125">(760) 594-1125</a>.'
  },
  {
    q: 'Do you service commercial refrigeration for restaurants in the P83 district?',
    a: 'Yes. P83 is one of the West Valley\'s most active dining and entertainment corridors, and the restaurants and bars there depend on commercial refrigeration that does not fail. Walk-in coolers, beer caves, reach-in refrigerators, ice machines, and bar cooling systems — we service all of it, with 24/7 emergency response. A restaurant\'s walk-in going down on a Friday night is our Friday night too. Call <a href="tel:+17605941125">(760) 594-1125</a> immediately.'
  },
  {
    q: 'My Peoria home AC can\'t keep up on the hottest days. What is likely wrong?',
    a: 'In Peoria\'s established neighborhoods, the most common causes are a failing compressor losing capacity with age, low refrigerant from a slow leak, or a dirty condenser coil (very common in desert environments). In newer Vistancia or Lake Pleasant area homes, undersizing from builder-grade installation is a frequent culprit. John Rigo will diagnose the actual issue — not just recommend the most expensive fix.'
  },
  {
    q: 'Do you service homes near Lake Pleasant Regional Park?',
    a: 'Yes. The residential communities north of Peoria near Lake Pleasant — including Vistancia and surrounding neighborhoods — are part of our service area. These tend to be newer homes with builder-grade equipment, and the drive north of the 101 means many HVAC companies from the Valley\'s east side deprioritize them. We don\'t. Call <a href="tel:+17605941125">(760) 594-1125</a>.'
  },
  {
    q: 'Do you service commercial properties in the Arrowhead area of Peoria?',
    a: 'Yes. The Arrowhead area — along Bell Road and the 101 — has significant retail and commercial development, including restaurants, grocery anchors, and the commercial density around Arrowhead Towne Center. We serve commercial HVAC and refrigeration throughout this corridor. Emergency refrigeration service available 24/7 for businesses in the Arrowhead area.'
  }
];
---

<Layout
  title="AC Repair in Peoria, AZ — Altered Air | (760) 594-1125"
  description="AC repair in Peoria, AZ — P83 commercial refrigeration, Lake Pleasant area, Happy Valley Road, Arrowhead, Vistancia. 35-40 min from Buckeye. Altered Air (760) 594-1125."
  canonical="/locations/peoria-az"
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> → Locations → Peoria, AZ</p>
      <h1>AC Repair in Peoria, AZ — Altered Air</h1>
      <p>
        AC repair in Peoria, AZ covers one of the West Valley's most varied cities — from the
        entertainment and dining corridor at P83 to the residential communities near Lake Pleasant
        and the established neighborhoods around Arrowhead. Altered Air serves all of Peoria from
        our Buckeye base, about 35–40 minutes southwest, with same-day AC repair, 24/7 emergency
        response, and commercial refrigeration service for P83's restaurants and the businesses
        along Happy Valley Road and Bell Road.
      </p>
      <a href="tel:+17605941125" class="phone-link">&#128222; Call (760) 594-1125</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">

      <h2>Peoria Summer Heat — 110°F+ and No Shortcut Around It</h2>
      <p>
        Peoria stretches from the older established neighborhoods along Bell Road up through
        newer communities near Lake Pleasant and beyond. Regardless of where in the city you
        are, summer temperatures in Peoria run 110–115°F during peak weeks — and in the northern,
        more desert-exposed communities near Lake Pleasant, some of the most intense heat in
        the metro. There is no neighborhood in Peoria where a summer AC failure is anything
        less than urgent.
      </p>
      <p>
        Maricopa County's annual heat-related death toll is the highest of any county in the
        country, and it reflects heat exposure across the entire metro — including Peoria's
        large residential population. Elderly residents, young children, and anyone without
        transportation to a cooling center face the highest risk when AC fails indoors. An
        AC failure in Peoria in July is a medical situation, and Altered Air treats it that way.
      </p>
      <p>
        John Rigo answers the phone on emergency calls. When a Peoria resident calls at 10 p.m.
        because their AC stopped and they have elderly parents visiting, that call gets personal
        attention — not a call center and a 48-hour appointment window.
      </p>

      <div class="content-two-col" style="margin-top:2.5rem;">
        <div>
          <h2>P83, Arrowhead, Vistancia, and the Communities We Know</h2>
          <p>
            P83 — the entertainment and dining district anchored along 83rd Avenue north of
            Bell Road — is one of the West Valley's primary commercial destinations. The
            concentration of restaurants, bars, sports venues, and entertainment businesses
            creates significant demand for commercial refrigeration and HVAC service. Walk-in
            coolers for restaurant kitchens, beer caves and tap systems for bars, ice machines
            running at high volume during summer — P83 businesses need equipment that works
            and a contractor who responds after hours when it does not.
          </p>
          <p>
            The Arrowhead area of Peoria — centered on the Bell Road and 101 corridor — has
            one of the Valley's strongest retail concentrations outside of Scottsdale. Arrowhead
            Towne Center, the surrounding restaurant row, and the commercial development stretching
            along Happy Valley Road all generate HVAC and refrigeration service demand. Grocery
            stores, restaurants, and food retailers in this corridor depend on cold chain equipment
            that does not fail at 115°F ambient temperature.
          </p>
          <p>
            Vistancia is Peoria's master-planned community in the northern hills — a large-scale
            development with homes ranging from entry-level to high-end estate properties. Many
            Vistancia homes are newer construction with builder-grade HVAC equipment that faces
            its real test in the first couple of Arizona summers. The community sits at a slightly
            higher elevation than central Peoria, which moderates heat marginally but does not
            eliminate the need for properly functioning AC.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="highlight-box">
            <h3>AC &amp; Refrigeration in Peoria</h3>
            <p>
              Serving P83, Lake Pleasant area, Arrowhead, Vistancia, and all of Peoria
              from our Buckeye base — 35–40 minutes away. Emergency calls always answered.
            </p>
            <a href="tel:+17605941125" class="phone">(760) 594-1125</a>
            <a href="tel:+17605941125" class="btn-primary" style="margin-top:0.5rem;">Call Now</a>
          </div>
          <div class="card" style="margin-top:1.5rem;">
            <h3>P83 Restaurant &amp; Bar Refrigeration</h3>
            <p>
              Commercial refrigeration for P83's restaurants and bars — walk-in coolers,
              ice machines, reach-in units, beer systems. Emergency service 24/7, because
              your walk-in does not fail on a Tuesday morning.
            </p>
            <a href="/services/refrigeration-repair" class="card-link">Commercial Refrigeration →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 style="margin-top:3rem;">Lake Pleasant Area, Peoria Sports Complex, and Happy Valley</h2>
      <p>
        The communities north of the 101 near Lake Pleasant Regional Park are among Peoria's
        most rapidly developing areas. The park itself draws significant recreational traffic,
        and the residential communities surrounding it include Vistancia and a series of newer
        subdivisions where builder-grade HVAC is the norm. Many homeowners in these communities
        are discovering what every West Valley new-construction owner eventually learns: minimum-code
        HVAC sizing performs differently in actual Arizona summer conditions than it does on paper.
      </p>
      <p>
        Peoria Sports Complex — spring training home of the San Diego Padres and Seattle Mariners —
        generates significant commercial activity in the surrounding Peoria Stadium corridor.
        Restaurants and sports bars near the complex run high refrigeration loads, particularly
        during spring training season and weekend events. Altered Air provides commercial
        refrigeration and HVAC service for the stadium area corridor as part of our regular
        Peoria service.
      </p>
      <p>
        Happy Valley Road has developed into one of the northwest Valley's primary commercial
        corridors, with restaurants, retail anchors, and business parks extending from the 51
        west to the 101. These businesses need commercial refrigeration they can count on,
        and Altered Air provides it. Call <a href="tel:+17605941125">(760) 594-1125</a>
        for commercial refrigeration service anywhere in Peoria.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-gray">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Services We Provide in Peoria, AZ</h2>
      <div class="service-list">
        <div class="service-item">
          <h3><a href="/services/ac-repair">AC Repair</a></h3>
          <p>Same-day AC repair throughout Peoria — P83 area, Arrowhead, Vistancia, Lake Pleasant communities, and all residential neighborhoods.</p>
